To create a ROS node in C++, you need to follow these steps:

1. Include the necessary headers:
   ```cpp
   #include "ros/ros.h"
   #include "std_msgs/String.h"
   #include <sstream>
   ```

2. Initialize the node and set a unique name:
   ```cpp
   ros::init(argc, argv, "example1_a");
   ```

3. Create a NodeHandle, which is the main access point for communication with the ROS system:
   ```cpp
   ros::NodeHandle n;
   ```

4. Set up a publisher by specifying the topic name and message type, along with the buffer size:
   ```cpp
   ros::Publisher pub = n.advertise<std_msgs::String>("message", 1000);
   ```

These steps will help you create a basic ROS node in C++.

